items.content: Please read the text about Canada and do the exercises

content.body: A dividing line between two countries
Another word for the coast of a country
Anyone who lives in a country
People living in a country who have a passport for that country
A measurement of how cold or warm it is outside
a way that people make money

prompt.body: Why is the Canadian one dollar coin called a "loonie"?

content.body: Because it has a loon on it
Because there are many different animals in Canada
Who does Canada have a good relationship with?
How many provinces and territories are in Canada?

prompt.body: Based on the information in this lesson, which statement is true?

content.body: Canada was established a very long time ago
There was no one living in Canada when it was discovered.

prompt.body: Based on the information in this lesson, which statement is false?

content.body: There are parts in Canada where peopl speak English and French
Only English is spoken in Canada

prompt.body: "Canada produces half of the world's maple syrup"

content.body: We don't know, the text doesn't mention it

items.content: Once you are done with the questions, please watch the video by Geography Now about Canada. You can turn on Closed Captions (CC) down and to the right if you want to read along.
